description.originalText: Camille has been an absolute lifesaver for our family. Camille has babysitting our boy over the last year, since when he was 4 months old. Camille's reliability and professionalism are outstanding, and her natural ability to connect with our baby is truly heartwarming. Camille's attentiveness and genuine concern make us feel at ease even when we are away. We can't thank her enough and she's been an essential part of our family support system.

description.displayText: Camille was everything I could imagine in a Nanny and more. My wife and I were in New York city temporarily and needed someone to look after our son for the week, full time, while we were otherwise occupied.   Camille was super flexible and met our needs perfectly.  If we needed her early one day or later another, she made it work.  During her time with our son, Camille took every opportunity to find activities and things to do around the city.  In a week, they explored multiple parks, a marionette puppet show, museums and even an orchestra concert, plus so much more.  My son will always remember our trip to NYC fondly because of everything Camille was able to do for us.   She is amazing!

description.displayText: My husband and I took a weekend trip to NYC in Sept. 2019. We hired Camille to watch our 8-year-old son in a hotel room while we attended a night-time event. We found her to be calm and kind but firm. She played some quiet activities with our son as he was winding down, and we returned to find him sleeping. We felt very comfortable leaving our child with Camille and would recommend her to others.

description.displayText: We visited NY and needed a nanny last minute. Camille was very professional and fast in her communications ahead of our visit, which was much appreciated. She took care of my 5-year-old daughter from 8.30am - 5.30pm and everything went great. She arrived early and my daughter immediately felt at ease. She brought some arts & crafts materials to keep my daughter occupied and took her to the Children's Museum by subway. She sent me updates during the day and asked a few questions when needed. I am really grateful that she took such great care of my daughter and would definitely hire her again.

description.displayText:
Camille took care of our son from July 14, 2015 to February 22, 2016. He was almost 18 months in July 2015. He made significant progress during this time learning from scratch the alphabet, counting to 20, over 100 words and putting his first 2-3 words sentences together. Also, Camille taught him good manners (e.g. being patient while waiting, not throwing things or poking) and layered the foundation for developing life lasting good habits (e.g. washing hands after using potty, brushing teeth after meals). Very energetic and familiar with the best activities for children NYC has to offer, Camille took our son daily to Central Park, Nolan Library, Met Museum, the playgrounds in the neighborhood, within the distance limits we felt comfortable. Camille made helpful suggestions on options for classes to enroll our son and she took him to attend these. Proactive, she also arranged for playdates. While in-door she creatively organized the time between reading books, play, art and crafts activities and needed time-out. Although cooking was an optional duty, she regularly cooked organic vegetarian food for our son to help with transition to solid foods. Camille is always punctual and never called in-sick. The expense budget she managed wisely, making very inspired selections of books, art supplies, toys, clothes and healthy foods. She will give us helpful reminders of the items low in stock or buy them if we run out. She will keep us updated during the day with pictures and text messages and also she will keep a written log of the daily activities. Camille values her independence as a caregiver and teacher to facilitate the guidance of the child she cares for through different stages of development. Please feel free to contact us with any questions.     

Thank you,
Oana
